name: Cicilline, David
message: In the coming weeks and months, we will have an opportunity to further explore these remedies. I am hopeful that, with @JoeBiden in the White House, we will finally end this monopoly moment and restore a free and open internet.

name: Cicilline, David
message: Finally, to revive antitrust enforcement, which has been dormant for too long, we should consider regular merger retrospectives and civil penalties for unfair methods of competition.

name: Cicilline, David
message: Second, to strengthen existing antitrust laws, we should consider updating Clayton Act and the Sherman Act, along with other measures to strengthen overall enforcement.

name: Cicilline, David
message: First, to restore competition in the digital economy, among other options, we should consider structural separations and prohibitions on certain dominant platforms from operating in adjacent lines of business.

name: Cicilline, David
message: In light of these facts, there is a clear and compelling need for Congress to take action. To that end, we are proposing a menu of policy options around three key objectives.

name: Cicilline, David
message: And third, these platforms abuse their control to expand their power. Whether it‚Äôs through self-preferencing, predatory pricing, or requiring users to buy additional products, the dominant platforms have used their power in destructive ways in order to grow even bigger.

name: Cicilline, David
message: Second, each platform uses its gatekeeper position to protect its power. By controlling the infrastructure of the digital age, they have surveilled other businesses to identify potential rivals‚Äîand ultimately bought out, copied, or cut off their competitive threats.

name: Cicilline, David
message: First, Amazon, Apple, Facebook, and Google each serves as a gatekeeper over a key channel of distribution in the economy, allowing them to pick winners and losers. They each abuse their power through exorbitant fees, oppressive contracts, and extracting valuable data.

name: Cicilline, David
message: This has been a thorough, top to bottom review of the state of competition in the digital economy. Our investigation has confirmed three key findings.

name: Cicilline, David
message: Today, after a 16-month long investigation, the House Antitrust Subcommittee is releasing our report on the state of competition in the digital marketplace. You can read it here. https://t.co/PaEgLmAr7W
